1
00:00:35,244 --> 00:00:38,539
（朝鲜 两年前）

2
00:00:51,550 --> 00:00:52,733
请让我回家
Please let me go home.

3
00:00:52,833 --> 00:00:54,470
求你了 我不是你们想的那种人
Please, I'm not who you think I am.

4
00:00:54,848 --> 00:00:57,100
我真的不是你们想的那种人
I'm really not who you think I am.

5
00:00:57,976 --> 00:01:00,061
求你了 我不是间谍
Please. Please. I'm not a spy.

6
00:01:00,220 --> 00:01:02,121
- 你是间谍  - 我不是间谍
- You are a spy. - I'm not a spy.

7
00:01:02,151 --> 00:01:03,360
求你让我回家吧
Please let me go home.

8
00:01:03,492 --> 00:01:05,194
再试一次
Try again.

9
00:01:05,233 --> 00:01:06,943
我不是间谍 我是生意人
I am not a spy. I am a businesswoman.

10
00:01:07,110 --> 00:01:09,660
我是润克石油公司的员工
I work for Rink Petroleum and Gas.

11
00:01:10,238 --> 00:01:12,657
请跟他们联络 润克石油公司
Please call them. I work for Rink Petroleum.

12
00:01:12,820 --> 00:01:15,966
你是来破坏我们的核子设施的
You are here to sabotage our nuclear ambitions.

13
00:01:16,033 --> 00:01:16,910
对吧？
Yes?

14
00:01:17,078 --> 00:01:19,998
我不是间谍！我不是间谍！
I am not a spy! I am not a spy!

15
00:01:34,512 --> 00:01:36,598
我不是间谍
I am not a spy.

16
00:01:36,931 --> 00:01:39,851
我不是间谍
I am not a spy.

17
00:01:40,143 --> 00:01:45,815
由于我亲爱领袖的恩惠与宽宏
It is through the grace and munificence of our glorious Dear Leader

18
00:01:46,399 --> 00:01:49,569
朝鲜民主主义人民共和国…
that the Democratic People's Republic of Korea

19
00:01:49,736 --> 00:01:53,323
赦免美国帝国主义者
has pardoned the American imperialist

20
00:01:53,490 --> 00:01:57,577
对我社会主义国家采取的敌对行为
for her hostile acts against our socialist nation.

21
00:01:57,744 --> 00:02:01,289
压低头 交换前一句话也别说
Keep your head down. Don't say anything till we make the swap.

22
00:02:02,207 --> 00:02:05,084
以防金正日改变心意
In case Kim Jong II here changes his mind.

23
00:02:19,641 --> 00:02:21,059
交换
Exchange.

24
00:02:21,267 --> 00:02:23,311
向右转
Right face!

25
00:02:26,689 --> 00:02:28,650
向右转
Right face!

26
00:02:28,983 --> 00:02:31,277
我不懂
I don't understand.

27
00:02:31,444 --> 00:02:33,696
你不懂什么？
You don't understand what?

28
00:02:35,740 --> 00:02:38,368
所有指示都说要丢下我
All the rules say to leave me, that one life

29
00:02:38,535 --> 00:02:41,287
不值得为一个人暴露组织行动
is not worth blowing operational cover.

30
00:02:41,454 --> 00:02:42,664
你没搞错
You got that right.

31
00:02:43,122 --> 00:02:46,835
必要时 我们会为大我牺牲小我
If we have to lose someone for the greater good, we will.

32
00:02:47,001 --> 00:02:48,044
那为什么救我？
So why did you do it?

33
00:02:49,254 --> 00:02:52,048
我没救你
Well, I didn't do it.

34
00:02:53,132 --> 00:02:54,801
是他
He did.

35
00:02:56,135 --> 00:02:59,013
他一发现你下落 就拼命设法救你
Once he found out where you were, there was no stopping him.

36
00:03:01,140 --> 00:03:03,768
他向国会议员和国务院请愿
He petitioned the Senate, the State Department.

37
00:03:03,935 --> 00:03:06,980
我们不要媒体注目 所以我们想
We didn't need the publicity so I figured we better do something

38
00:03:07,146 --> 00:03:10,692
再不设法 他会自己进攻这个烂国家
or he's gonna invade this goddamn rice-paddy republic himself.

39
00:03:27,625 --> 00:03:29,252
你还好吧？
You okay?

40
00:03:31,337 --> 00:03:32,839
还好
Yeah.

41
00:03:49,839 --> 00:03:53,509
（华盛顿 现在）

42
00:04:20,170 --> 00:04:21,125
早上好
Good morning.

43
00:04:21,299 --> 00:04:22,590
结婚纪念日快乐
Happy anniversary.

44
00:04:24,974 --> 00:04:26,809
要我帮你准备早餐吗？
You want me to make you breakfast?

45
00:04:26,976 --> 00:04:29,395
吃松饼如何？
How about pancakes?

46
00:04:29,562 --> 00:04:31,522
你亲手做？
Your cooking?

47
00:04:31,814 --> 00:04:33,691
开玩笑 你很爱吃我做的
You're joking. You like my cooking.

48
00:04:33,858 --> 00:04:35,860
德国人不开玩笑的
Germans don't joke.

49
00:04:36,861 --> 00:04:38,988
波特喜欢我的料理
Burt likes my cooking.

50
00:04:46,663 --> 00:04:48,081
把你的虫收起来
Get your bugs off the table.

51
00:04:48,247 --> 00:04:50,333
- 这是蜘蛛  - 蜘蛛就是虫
- They're spiders. - They're bugs.

52
00:04:51,334 --> 00:04:53,378
- 这是蜘蛛  - 蜘蛛就是虫
- They're spiders. - They're bugs.

53
00:04:58,250 --> 00:04:59,812
把下层折回来
Fold the next layer back

54
00:04:59,903 --> 00:05:01,853
像前两个一样
as you did the two before it.

55
00:05:02,510 --> 00:05:03,920
把餐巾转过来
Turn the napkin over.

56
00:05:04,651 --> 00:05:06,090
将两端向后折
Fold both sides back,

57
00:05:06,265 --> 00:05:09,102
在三分之一的地方重复
and over one another about a third of the way.

58
00:05:10,770 --> 00:05:12,347
检查是否对称
Check for symmetry

59
00:05:12,457 --> 00:05:14,600
再仔细折妥
and press the fold down well.

60
00:05:14,774 --> 00:05:16,901
你上班时间搞这个？
Are you doing this on company time?

61
00:05:17,060 --> 00:05:19,095
并且插入你最喜欢的银器…
And insert your favorite silverware...

62
00:05:19,186 --> 00:05:20,730
今天是我结婚纪念日
It's my anniversary.

63
00:05:21,406 --> 00:05:24,242
我要一切完美
And I want it to be perfect.

64
00:05:24,409 --> 00:05:27,620
不过这并不性感
But that is not sexy.

65
00:05:28,329 --> 00:05:30,498
对 不过这很实用
No, but it is utilitarian.

66
00:05:30,665 --> 00:05:32,834
这年头实用就代表性感
And utilitarian is the new sexy.

67
00:05:33,584 --> 00:05:36,587
确定身份了 他叫乌珊奥萨耶夫
I ran the trace. First name Usam, last name Utsaev.

68
00:05:36,750 --> 00:05:37,845
确实线索？
Any verifiable hits?

69
00:05:37,977 --> 00:05:38,684
有一个
One.

70
00:05:38,764 --> 00:05:41,431
弗朗西斯 帮个忙把报告锁好 明天再说
Francis, do me a favor and stick that in the safe till tomorrow.

71
00:05:41,926 --> 00:05:44,012
这位女神今晚有大事要办
Mata Hari here's got a big night tonight.

72
00:05:44,178 --> 00:05:46,389
是 长官 马上办
Yes, sir. Right away, sir.

73
00:05:46,597 --> 00:05:49,517
“长官”？ 我的样子有那么专横吗？
"Sir"? Do I look like a "sir" to you?

74
00:05:49,684 --> 00:05:50,727
官架子十足
From head to toe.

75
00:05:51,561 --> 00:05:54,022
我很惊讶他没叫你“陛下”
I'm surprised he didn't call you "Your Majesty."

76
00:05:54,180 --> 00:05:55,591
我喜欢这个称呼
I like the ring of that.

77
00:05:55,903 --> 00:05:58,390
我想我喜欢人家叫我“陛下”
I think I'd prefer "Your Majesty."

78
00:05:59,402 --> 00:06:01,237
我以前也这么嫩吗？
Was I ever that young?

79
00:06:03,614 --> 00:06:04,699
比他更嫩
Younger.

80
00:06:05,491 --> 00:06:07,201
陪我出去
Walk me out.

81
00:06:08,286 --> 00:06:10,204
总统办公室的简报如何？
How did the Oval Office briefing go?

82
00:06:10,371 --> 00:06:12,206
你知道的 跟往常一样
Oh, you know. The usual.

83
00:06:12,770 --> 00:06:16,091
总统想知道俄罗斯事件发生前一天的详情
President wants to know what's happening in Russia the day before it happens.

84
00:06:16,772 --> 00:06:18,673
你呢？听说面谈很顺利
How about you? I heard that interview went well.

85
00:06:19,088 --> 00:06:20,798
老天保佑
Fingers crossed.

86
00:06:21,466 --> 00:06:23,217
你确定要换位子？
You sure about this?

87
00:06:23,384 --> 00:06:26,345
一旦去做行政人员就不能回头了
You know, once you start pushing paper, there's no turning back.

88
00:06:26,512 --> 00:06:29,891
我上次出任务时有个超怪的感觉
I had the strangest feeling when I was out last time.

89
00:06:30,050 --> 00:06:31,332
我得了思乡病
I was homesick.

90
00:06:31,547 --> 00:06:32,510
思乡病？
Homesick?

91
00:06:32,685 --> 00:06:35,021
- 不能吃药解决吗？ - 长官！长官！
- Can't you take something for that?  - Sir! Sir!

92
00:06:37,230 --> 00:06:38,400
有自首的
We got a walk-in.

93
00:06:38,827 --> 00:06:40,000
是个逃兵 十分钟前
A defector, 10 minutes ago.

94
00:06:40,102 --> 00:06:40,670
在这里？
Here?

95
00:06:40,957 --> 00:06:42,270
我猜他不相信我们的伪装
I guess he's not buying our cover.

96
00:06:42,440 --> 00:06:43,746
查过背景了？
Did you get his bona fides?

97
00:06:43,928 --> 00:06:44,667
俄罗斯人
He's Russian.

98
00:06:44,841 --> 00:06:46,932
只宣称是前国安局探员
He says he's FSB but won't give us any more.

99
00:06:47,158 --> 00:06:49,118
- 他很怪  - 他英文如何？
- He's a strange guy. - How's his English?

100
00:06:49,702 --> 00:06:51,412
还可以
Passable. Not great.

101
00:06:51,579 --> 00:06:54,457
但是没办法很清楚的表达
But if it got down to the subtleties of English nuance...

102
00:06:54,620 --> 00:06:56,331
泰德 麦克在家等我
Ted, Mike's gonna be waiting for me.

103
00:06:56,438 --> 00:06:58,280
对 我也要赶飞机
Yeah, and I got a plane to catch.

104
00:06:58,419 --> 00:06:59,462
来吧 绍特
Come on, Salt.

105
00:06:59,629 --> 00:07:02,799
没有坏人能逃过你的法眼
No one can sort out a nutjob from the real thing faster than you.

106
00:07:02,965 --> 00:07:06,010
- 我只有25分钟  - 我有26分 走吧
- I got 25 minutes. - I got 26. Let's go.

107
00:07:11,933 --> 00:07:15,019
好吧 等我们有进展再决定
Yeah, okay. Well, we'll decide when we know more.

108
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:17,685
- 是谁找反情报组的？ - 不是我
- Who called Counterintelligence? - Not me.

109
00:07:17,812 --> 00:07:20,230
泰德 我们不请自来
Ted. We're crashing the party.

110
00:07:22,360 --> 00:07:23,324
皮博迪
Peabody.

111
00:07:23,415 --> 00:07:24,230
绍特
Salt.

112
00:07:29,242 --> 00:07:31,202
取下头套
Please remove the hood.

113
00:07:32,495 --> 00:07:33,913
麦克风打开
Microphones are on.

114
00:07:34,080 --> 00:07:36,040
检查读数
Checking levels.

115
00:07:37,458 --> 00:07:38,751
基准确定
Baseline recorded.

116
00:07:43,172 --> 00:07:45,967
启动神经扫描 准备好了
Neural scan is up. Ready to go.

117
00:07:47,800 --> 00:07:48,797
伊芙
Ev.

118
00:07:49,638 --> 00:07:50,220
好
Yeah.

119
00:07:50,388 --> 00:07:52,557
开始录音录像
Commencing audio and visual recording.

120
00:08:00,523 --> 00:08:02,692
测试耳机
Testing earpiece.

121
00:08:05,194 --> 00:08:08,239
会谈开始时间14点42分
Interview has commenced at 1442.

122
00:08:18,082 --> 00:08:20,042
你结婚了
You're married.

123
00:08:21,460 --> 00:08:24,589
对于一个女间谍来说
A husband must be a distraction

124
00:08:25,298 --> 00:08:28,384
丈夫是个绊脚石
for a female intelligence officer.

125
00:08:28,551 --> 00:08:30,720
我们要谈的是你
Well, we're here to talk about you.

126
00:08:30,928 --> 00:08:32,054
你叫什么名字？
So, what is your name?

127
00:08:33,806 --> 00:08:35,600
我叫
My name is

128
00:08:35,766 --> 00:08:40,146
奥列格·瓦塞利维奇·奥洛夫
Oleg Vassilyevich Orlov.

129
00:08:43,566 --> 00:08:45,568
我得了癌症
I have cancer.

130
00:08:45,735 --> 00:08:47,778
我真感动
I'm moved.

131
00:08:48,070 --> 00:08:50,072
一个投诚的癌症病患
A defector with cancer.

132
00:08:50,781 --> 00:08:54,285
你是想卖情报换化疗还是你只是怕死？
Are you selling secrets for chemo or are you afraid of dying?

133
00:08:54,452 --> 00:08:59,123
要说我的行动会得到什么报应
If I have gained anything by damning myself,

134
00:08:59,540 --> 00:09:05,379
就是我不再恐惧
it is that I no longer have anything to fear.

135
00:09:06,339 --> 00:09:09,008
俄罗斯也正面临死亡
Russia is also dying.

136
00:09:09,170 --> 00:09:10,496
不过不像我 她还没死
But unlike me, she's not dead.

137
00:09:10,609 --> 00:09:12,530
奥列格·瓦塞利·奥洛夫
Oleg Vassily Orlov,

138
00:09:12,762 --> 00:09:16,474
1993年出现于新西伯利亚
shows up in 1993 in Novosibirsk Oblast, Siberia.

139
00:09:16,682 --> 00:09:18,935
是前情报头子维多的手下
He was on Victor Barisovsky's staff there.

140
00:09:19,143 --> 00:09:20,394
他是国安局的人
He checks out as FSB, Ev.

141
00:09:20,561 --> 00:09:23,439
扫描显示癌症的事他没说谎
Scan says he's truthful on the cancer.

142
00:09:23,814 --> 00:09:25,024
93年以前呢？
Prior to '93?

143
00:09:25,274 --> 00:09:27,318
俄罗斯原本强大
Russia was once strong, powerful...

144
00:09:27,485 --> 00:09:29,987
晗都没有 他根本不存在
Nothing. He doesn't exist.

145
00:09:30,154 --> 00:09:33,908
等一切回复原本正确的轨道
And she will be again when things have been set back

146
00:09:34,116 --> 00:09:36,077
她也将再度强大
on the correct path.

147
00:09:36,327 --> 00:09:39,038
我有别的地方要去 奥洛夫先生
I have somewhere I need to be, Mr. Orlov,

148
00:09:39,205 --> 00:09:41,791
不介意的话 请切入重点
so if you wouldn't mind getting to the point.

149
00:09:45,001 --> 00:09:48,209
我来是要告诉你一个故事

150
00:09:49,130 --> 00:09:50,916
我不喜欢听故事

151
00:09:51,340 --> 00:09:53,877
不过我还是会听的

152
00:09:54,011 --> 00:09:55,930
请说英文
In English, please.

153
00:09:56,555 --> 00:09:57,890
其他人也在听
Others are listening.

154
00:09:58,849 --> 00:10:01,811
1975年
1975.

155
00:10:02,270 --> 00:10:04,522
冷战时期
The Cold War.

156
00:10:06,232 --> 00:10:08,109
在格洛斯尼一个体育馆里
In a gymnasium in Grozny,

157
00:10:08,276 --> 00:10:10,528
一位苏联的奥运摔角选手
a Soviet Olympic wrestler

158
00:10:10,695 --> 00:10:14,240
沙夏契诃夫
named Sasha Fyorodovich Chenkov

159
00:10:14,865 --> 00:10:16,325
初次邂逅
meets for the first time

160
00:10:16,909 --> 00:10:20,830
当代唯一女性西洋棋大师
the only female chess grand master of her era:

161
00:10:22,248 --> 00:10:25,710
安雅纽伦科娃
Anja Nurekyova.

162
00:10:26,002 --> 00:10:29,088
一个月内 他们就闪电结婚了
Within a month, they were married.

163
00:10:29,255 --> 00:10:32,717
然后一年内 生了一个孩子
And within a year, a child.

164
00:10:33,301 --> 00:10:35,303
一个月后
One month more,

165
00:10:35,460 --> 00:10:37,428
那孩子被送回…
the child was back...

166
00:10:37,743 --> 00:10:39,510
原来出生的医院
in the same hospital,

167
00:10:39,682 --> 00:10:41,058
高烧病重
sick with fever.

168
00:10:43,686 --> 00:10:45,980
之后过了几天
And within days after that,

169
00:10:46,147 --> 00:10:49,734
那孩子突然死了
the child suddenly was dead.

170
00:10:51,902 --> 00:10:55,781
对 有个孩子死了
Yes, a child was dead.

171
00:10:55,940 --> 00:10:57,235
而且是的
And, yes,

172
00:10:57,467 --> 00:11:00,160
有个孩子被埋葬了
a child was buried.

173
00:11:06,790 --> 00:11:08,885
不过契诃夫的孩子
But the Chenkov baby

174
00:11:09,153 --> 00:11:10,920
还活着
was alive...

175
00:11:11,080 --> 00:11:14,764
变成了另一个人的资产
and became the property of another man.

176
00:11:15,880 --> 00:11:17,459
这位间谍大师
A master spy...

177
00:11:17,616 --> 00:11:20,184
设计了一个伟大计划
who had devised the greatest plan

178
00:11:20,256 --> 00:11:24,182
一个俄国爱国者的终极计划
a Russian patriot could ever invent.

179
00:11:24,680 --> 00:11:28,422
一个摧毁美国的计划
A plan to destroy America.

180
00:11:29,815 --> 00:11:31,650
一切始于…
It had all started...

181
00:11:31,817 --> 00:11:35,780
一位美国人 叫李·哈维·奥斯华
with an American named Lee Harvey Oswald.

182
00:11:35,940 --> 00:11:37,666
1959年
In 1959,

183
00:11:37,900 --> 00:11:40,070
他移民到俄国
he emigrated to Russia.

184
00:11:40,240 --> 00:11:41,486
三年后
Three years later,

185
00:11:41,751 --> 00:11:43,160
他返回了家乡
he returned home.

186
00:11:43,329 --> 00:11:46,123
不过回到美国的那个人
But the man who came back to America

187
00:11:46,290 --> 00:11:49,340
事实上 是一位俄国间谍
was in fact a Russian spy...

188
00:11:49,511 --> 00:11:51,750
叫亚列克
named Alek.

189
00:11:52,129 --> 00:11:55,674
在1963年11月22日
On November 22nd, 1963,

190
00:11:55,841 --> 00:11:58,994
亚列克成为新计划第一位成功者
Alek became the first success of the new program

191
